average production prices have been calculated by using
sales quantities from the corporations own production as the divisor. average
production costs have been computed by using net production quantities for the
divisor. the volumes of crude oil and natural gas liquids (ngl) production used
for this computation are shown in the oil and gas production table in section
3.a. the volumes of natural gas used in the calculation are the production
volumes of natural gas available for sale and are also shown in section 3.a.
the natural gas available for sale volumes are different from those shown in
the reserves table in the oil and gas reserves part of the supplemental
information on oil and gas exploration and production activities portion of
the financial section of this report due to volumes consumed or flared. gas is
converted to an oil-equivalent basis at six million cubic feet per one thousand
barrels.
