totaled $30.3 billion in 2015, $14.8 billion lower than 2014. the major source
of funds was net income including noncontrolling interests of $16.6 billion, a
decrease of $17.1 billion. the noncash provision for depreciation and depletion
was $18.0 billion, up $0.8 billion from the prior year. the adjustment for net
gains on asset sales was $0.2 billion compared to an adjustment of $3.2 billion
in 2014. changes in operational working capital, excluding cash and debt,
decreased cash in 2015 by $3.1 billion.
